   - This shows how the allocator consumes blocks from the free list

3. **Deallocation Demonstration**:
   - `deallocate()` calls `push()` internally to add a block to the head of the free list
   - This shows how the allocator returns blocks to the free list

4. **Free List Behavior**: The sequence demonstrates the LIFO (Last-In-First-Out) nature of the free list management:
   - `push()` adds to the head (most recently deallocated block)
   - `pop()` removes from the head (next available block)

